-- India Plans 500 Billion Rupee Debt Fund for Power Investments, Mint Says
-- Victoria Batchelor
-- 2010-07-27T01:12:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/india-plans-500-billion-rupee-debt-fund-for-power-investments-mint-says.html

          
          
              India’s government plans to create a
500 billion rupee debt fund to finance power projects, the Mint
reported, citing Power Secretary P. Umashankar. The fund is in
the process of being formulated and will be in the form of
“‘takeout’’ financing, the newspaper said.  
